'''Aleph''' is a 1980s [[Italo disco]] band, featuring the vocals of [[Dave Rodgers]]. The other members of the group were [[Donato Bellini]] and [[Marco Manzi]]. They achieved a fair amount of success with the single "Fly To Me" in 1985, which reached the Top Ten in several countries. They released two LPs, "Black Out" in 1988 and "Take My Life" in 1989, both originally released on Time Records. The group later released three songs in the late 1990s.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.daverodgers.it/SiteNew/html/bio.htm |title=Dave Rodgers - Official Web Site |access-date=2007-02-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928080828/http://www.daverodgers.it/SiteNew/html/bio.htm |archive-date=2007-09-28 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>[http://www.discogs.com/artist/Aleph Aleph discography at Discogs]</ref>
