{{Infobox language family |name=Bafia |ethnicity= |region= |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Southern Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] ([[Guthrie classification of Bantu languages#Zone A|Zone A.50]]) |glotto=bafi1244 |glottorefname=Bafia (A.50) }}
The '''Bafia languages''' are a clade of [[Bantu language]]s coded Zone A.50 in Guthrie's classification. According to Nurse & Philippson (2003), the languages form a valid node. They are: :[[Fa’ language|Fa’]] (Lefa), [[Kaalong language|Kaalong]] (Dimbong), [[Kpa language|Kpa]] (Bafia), [[Ngayaba language|Ngayaba]] (Tibea) [[Hijuk language|Hijuk]] was listed as unclassified A.50 in Guthrie, but according to ''Ethnologue'' it is quite similar to [[Basaa language|Basaa]].
