'''Domaine Raspail-Ay''' is a [[French wine]] [[winery|estate]]   in the southern [[Rhône (wine region)|Rhône wine region]] of [[France]].<ref>[https://www.vivino.com/wineries/raspail/wines/gigondas-2014 Gigondas 2014]</ref> It carries the [[Gigondas AOC]] ''[[Appellation d'Origine Contrôlée|appellation]]'' and is located in the commune of [[Gigondas]], in [[Vaucluse]].
The [[red wine]] blend bottled at the estate is 80% [[Grenache]], 15% [[Syrah]] and 5% [[Mourvèdre]], and is generally 14%-15% [[alcohol by volume|alcohol]].<ref name="Wine month" /> Domaine Raspail-Ay is a small estate of just 40 acres, and produces no more than 8,000 cases each vintage.<ref name="Wine month">[https://www.winemonthclub.com/domaine-raspail-ay-gigondas-2014.htm Domaine Raspail-Ay]</ref>
The wine is [[Sweetness of wine|dry]], with medium/full [[Wine tasting descriptors|body]].<ref>[https://vinchicago.com/wines/6309-detail Domaine Raspail-Ay 2014] Vin Chicago</ref>

Being a little brother of [[Châteauneuf-du-Pape AOC|Châteauneuf-du-Pape]], Gigondas AOC is moderately [[wikt:prestige|prestigious]] and can [[aging wine|age]] well when treated with care.<ref>Niels Lillelund: ''Rhône-Vinene'' JP Bøger - JP/Politikens Forlagshus A/S, 2004. {{ISBN|87-567-7140-1}}, p. 151-161</ref>

