{{france-stub}}

'''Duckefett''' is a simple [[sauce]] and a regional specialty in northern [[Hesse]], [[Germany]], particularly in [[Kassel]]. It is made of [[bacon]], [[onion]]s, [[sour cream]] and occasionally cooked and [[condensed milk]] added. As for side dishes, they are usually Duckefett potatoes, potato dumplings, served occasionally. Because of the low-cost ingredients Duckefett was long considered "poor man's food".{{Citation needed|date=April 2012}}

