The '''National Assembly''' ({{lang-fr|Assemblée Nationale}}) is the [[lower house]] of the [[bicameralism|bicameral]] [[Parliament of the Republic of the Congo]]. It has 139 members, elected for a five-year term in single-seat [[constituency|constituencies]].
==Latest elections== {{main article|Republic of the Congo parliamentary election, 2012}} {| class=wikitable style=text-align:right !Party !Votes !% !Seats !+/– |- |align=left|[[Congolese Party of Labour]]|| || ||89||+43 |- |align=left|[[Congolese Movement for Democracy and Integral Development]]|| || ||7||–4 |- |align=left|[[Pan-African Union for Social Democracy]]|| || ||7||–4 |- |align=left|Other parties allied with the PCT|| || ||9||– |- |align=left|Independents allied with the PCT|| || ||12||– |- |align=left|Others|| || ||12||– |- |align=left|Vacant||–||–||3||– |- |align=left|'''Total'''|| || ||'''139'''||'''+2''' |- |align=left colspan=5|Source: [http://www.news24.com/Africa/News/Congo-ruling-party-wins-majority-in-parly-20120808 News 24] |}
