[[File:Salviati Planisphere.jpg|thumb|upright=1.35|right|The Salviati Planisphere]]

The '''Salviati Planisphere''' is a [[world map]] showing the [[Spanish Empire|Spanish]] view of the Earth's surface at the time of its creation {{circa}} 1525, and includes the eastern coasts of [[North America|North]] and [[South America]] and the [[Strait of Magellan|Straits of Magellan]]. Rather than include imagined material in unexplored areas—as was customary—it is content to leave them blank, inviting future exploration.

It is believed to have been drawn by [[Nuno Garcia de Toreno]], the head of the [[Casa de Contratación|Casa de la Contratacion]],  in [[Seville]]. It takes its name from Cardinal [[Giovanni Salviati]], the [[Nuncio|papal nuncio]] to Spain from 1525-30, who was given it by [[Charles V, Holy Roman Emperor|Holy Roman Emperor Charles V]], also [[King of Spain]] at the time.<ref>{{Cite book|title = The Mapping of the Entradas Into the Greater Southwest|last = Reinhartz|first = Dennis (editor)|publisher = University of Oklahoma Press|year = 1998|isbn = 0806130474|location = |pages = 62|url = https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=PX-WcAL_RQcC&pg=PA62&lpg=PA62&dq=salviati+planisphere&source=bl&ots=mceBJFrDGS&sig=S70YXogz1RTBCc5Vk3f4lKPO7mM&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CEYQ6AEwCWoVChMI4Nqxl7-8yAIVhbQUCh13HAL6#v=onepage&q=salviati%20planisphere&f=false}}</ref><ref name="Padrón2004">{{cite book|author=Ricardo Padrón|title=The Spacious Word: Cartography, Literature, and Empire in Early Modern Spain|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GxCv8jUEIsAC&pg=PA131|year=2004|publisher=University of Chicago Press|isbn=978-0-226-64433-2|page=131}}</ref><ref name="WolffColin1992">{{cite book|author1=Hans Wolff|author2=Susi Colin|title=America: early maps of the New World|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=m44OAQAAMAAJ|year=1992|publisher=Prestel|isbn=978-3-7913-1232-3|pages=48–49}}</ref>

It is currently located at the [[Laurentian Library|Biblioteca Medicea Laurenziana]], in [[Florence]], [[Italy]].<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://cartographic-images.net/Cartographic_Images/336_Salviati_Planisphere.html|title = Cartographic Images|date = |accessdate = |website = Number 336|publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref>

