{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}} [[File:Plowden.jpg|thumb|Plowden's grave, [[Gondar]]]]
'''Walter Charles Metcalf Chichele Plowden''' (3 August 1820&nbsp;– 13 March 1860)<ref name=rcp>{{cite book |last=Plowden |first=Walter F. C. Chicheley |date=1914 |title=Records of the Chicheley Plowdens, AD 1590–1913 |url= https://archive.org/details/recordsofchichel00plow |location=London |publisher=Heath, Cranton & Ouseley |via=The Internet Archive |accessdate=2014-08-11 }}</ref> was a British diplomat, consul at [[Massawa]] on the [[Red Sea]] coast from 1848 to his death. He played a role in [[Ethiopia|Ethiopian]] politics in the mid 19th-century: during his tenure he cultivated the friendship of first ''[[Ras (title)|Ras]]'' [[Ali II of Yejju|Ali]], and later the Ethiopian emperor [[Tewodros II of Ethiopia|Tewodros II]].
J. R. Hooker remarks that "as a political agent, Plowden was valuable; as a writer of travel literature he was engaging and intelligent; but as a consul he was useless, his commercial reports being limited to three in 1852. He was never at his post after 1855."<ref>Hooker, [https://www.jstor.org/stable/180000 "The Foreign Office and the 'Abyssinian Captives'", ''Journal of African History''], '''2''' (1961), p. 245</ref>
In 1860, Plowden was murdered during a journey between [[Gondar]] and the [[Red Sea]] by a follower of [[Agew Niguse]], a warlord hostile to Tewodros. Plowden was interred in the [[Royal Enclosure (Gondar)|Royal Enclosure]], next to the Gemjabet Mariyam church. His writings were published as ''Travels in Abyssinia and the Galla Country, with an account of a mission to Ras Ali in 1848'' by his brother in London in 1868.<ref name=travels>{{cite book |last=Plowden |first=Walter Chichele |editor-last=Plowden |editor-first=Trevor Chichele |date=1868 |title=Travels in Abyssinia and the Galla Country, with an account of a mission to Ras Ali in 1848 |url= https://archive.org/details/travelsinabyssin00plow |location=London |publisher=Longmans, Green and Co. |via=The Internet Archive |accessdate=2014-08-12 }}</ref>
